Let x be the number of people in the room.
Two-thirds of the people in a room are seated, so (2/3)*x of the people are seated.
The rest of the people, (1 - 2/3)*x = 1/3*x, are standing.
Three-fourths of the chairs are filled, so (3/4)*(x+6) are occupied.
0.75*(x+6) = 2/3*x
0.75x + 4.5 = (2/3)*x
3 * (0.75x + 4.5) = 2x
2.25x + 13.5 = 2x
0.25x = 13.5
x = 13.5 / 0.25
x = <<54=54>>54
There are 54 people in the room. Answer: \boxed{54}.
